cs.IOT, cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.NI 

This paper discusses data analytics for the Internet of Things (IoT), which is a subfield of computer science that deals with the interconnection of physical devices. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IOT. The paper also discusses distributed data analytics, which involves processing data on resource-constrained devices, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) another likely category. The paper also discusses data fusion techniques, which are used to extract features from raw data, making cs.DB (Databases) a possible category. The paper also discusses the need for quick responses and reducing network and storage resources, which are topics related to software engineering (cs.SE) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), respectively.
